com.xatkit.core.recognition.processor

Interface IntentPostProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnglishSentimentPostProcessor, IsEnglishYesNoQuestionPostProcessor, RemoveEnglishStopWordsPostProcessor, StanfordNLPPostProcessor

    public interface IntentPostProcessor
    Applies a post-processing function on the provided recognizedIntent.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default void init()
      Initializes the post-processor.
      com.xatkit.intent.RecognizedIntent process(com.xatkit.intent.RecognizedIntent recognizedIntent, XatkitSession session)

    • Method Detail

      • init

        default void init()
        Initializes the post-processor.

        This method is called after the construction of all the post-processors, and can be used to initialize services used by multiple post-processors (e.g. a NLP service that needs to be warmed-up).

        Sub-classes should override this method if they need to perform initialization steps that cannot be performed when constructing the post-processor.

      • process

        com.xatkit.intent.RecognizedIntent process(com.xatkit.intent.RecognizedIntent recognizedIntent,
                                           XatkitSession session)
        Processes the provided recognizedIntent.

        This method is called with the session associated to the provided recognizedIntent in order to define advanced post-processing functions taking into account session's content.

        Parameters:
        recognizedIntent - the RecognizedIntent to process
        session - the XatkitSession associated to the recognizedIntent
        Returns:
        the processed recognizedIntent
